    "description": "After calling the April selloff and the downside target in advance, I began writing more and more about a so-called ‘hidden QE’—which, by May, I started referring to as the ‘Bessent put’: a concealed support mechanism designed to sustain artificial growth, primarily via equity–yield correlation dynamics.",
    "body_json": null,
    "body_html": null,
    "truncated_body_text": "After calling the April selloff and the downside target in advance, I began writing more and more about a so-called ‘hidden QE’—which, by May, I started referring to as the ‘Bessent put’: a concealed support mechanism designed to sustain artificial growth, primarily via equity–yield correlation dynamics. As someone who both trades tactically in the short term and manages a long-term investment portfolio, this metric is one of my most important gauges of market sentiment.",
